gsx$addashortdescriptionofyourfilm750cha.$t:
Nowadays the word “quarantine” has become an inevitable part of our everyday conversations and lives. But where did the term originate?
Follow us in this short animated mini-documentary on the search for the linguistic roots of this omnipresent word in Croatia in the Middle Ages.

COVID-19 is dictating our daily lives all over the world. In March, the government ordered all cafés, bars and restaurants to close. The normal life is paused. 

This is my hometown Braunschweig, Germany, on Sunday 22nd March 2020.

On the 29th May my parents celebrated their 50th anniversary. For that we were planning to spent a few days in Spain. However the situation changed due to the pandemic and instead we managed to spent a few days at the seaside. It was the first time in months since I've seen my parents face to face (but keeping a distance) so those were special few days... The film demonstrates the tide approaching. I found it surprising how fast and inexorably the water moves...calm but steady and indifferent. A fascinating (but frail) ecosystem.

gsx$addashortdescriptionofyourfilm750cha.$t:
Die Lehrer und Boulespieler Thomas und Christoph sind wieder auf der Schillerhöhe in Marbach am Neckar, Geburtstort des Dichters Friedrich Schiller. Die beiden haben ihren neuen Alltag routiniert. Kaffee wurde rationiert. Auch gegärtnert wird inzwischen. Meinungen zur Kontaktsperre und Maskenpflicht. Und, wie gehen sie mit ihrer besonderen Lehrersituation um?

The teachers and boule players Thomas and Christoph are back on the Schillerhöhe in Marbach am Neckar, birthplace of the poet Friedrich Schiller. The two of them have gotten used to their new everyday life. Coffee has been rationed. There is also gardening in the meantime. Opinions on contact ban and compulsory masks. And, how do they deal with their special teacher situation?

gsx$yourfilmstitle.$t: LEHRE IN CORONA // TEACHING IN CORONA

gsx$addashortdescriptionofyourfilm750cha.$t:
16.4.-2.5.2020: Carmen unterrichtet an einem Gymnasium Mathe und Musik und ist allein erziehende Mutter. Nachbarin Annette ist Grundschullehrerin. Sie lebt mit ihren Söhnen und ihrem Mann zusammen. Während sich Annette überlegt, was sie für das Geld tun kann und wie der Glaube zu den Schülern kommt, hat Carmen nach anfänglichen "Coronaferien" viel Arbeit, den Unterricht digital zu organisieren.

Carmen teaches maths and music at a high school and is a single mother. Neighbor Annette is a primary school teacher. She lives with her sons and her husband. While Annette is thinking about what she can do for the money and how faith comes to the pupils, Carmen has a lot of work to organize the lessons digitally after the initial "corona holidays".

The Bauer family, a farming family, has been selling their products, especially fruit, at the market for many decades. The younger generation helps the older one, faith plays an important role. Market events in Corona times at a distance ...

Love locks during lockdown: Cologne, Germany, Hohenzollern-Bridge and Cologne Cathedral, March 27th, 2020, 12pm. Corona-Lockdown had been in effect since March 23rd. It's Friday at noon. The fourth day of the corona lockdown: At this day, only the many hundreds of love locks at the fence of the bridge bear witness to how busy and super-popular these places were before the lockdown. The love lock tradition: Lovers attach their lock at the bridge, then kiss each other - and throw the key into the river Rhine.

In der Altstadt von Marbach am Neckar sitzen die Profimusikerin und Stadträtin der Grünen Susanne Wichmann und der Antiquar und Schillervereinsvorsitzende Birger Laing vor dem Geburtshaus von Friedrich Schiller. Ohne Corona hätten sie sich nicht kennen gelernt. Zusammen veranstalten sie einige der sogenannten 1:1 concerts, die auf eine Idee der Künstlerin Marina Abramovic zurück gehen. Das gespendete Geld kommt freischaffenden Musikern zugute. Als Dritte im Bunde drehte ich gratis einen Werbefilm zur Unterstützung der concerts. Dabei habe ich die Gelegenheit genutzt, zwei Marbacher "Funktionsträger" zu ihrer Einschätzung der Krise zu befragen. Persönliches und Gesellschaftsrelevantes kam zur Sprache.

The is film, which title is narrating more clear of the films circumstances than itself, is produced and presented by the artist Jos Diegel, although in 2020 in times of Quarantine due to the worldwide pandemic, this Film has been created collectively within a workshop lead by the artist Jos Diegel at "Schule fьr unabhдgigen Film“ (school for independent film) in Frankfurt, which is headed by Arnd Tibor Koch. Analogue 35mm and 16mm Filmmaterial has been painted and scratched on by the students during the experimental film art class. The collective film production and experience offers a playful and artistic approach into filmmaking itself and teaches the visual basics of filmtechnic and material.
